			<dt class="comment ">
		<span class="comment_author"><a href='http://www.burntfingerbbq.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Jason</a></span>
		<span class="comment_time">January 28, 2009</span>
		</dt>
		<dd class="comment ">
		<div class="format_text">
		<p>@Jon &#8211; Indirect heat is the key to grilling this bad boy.  Turn off at least half the burners and set it above those.  You may even want to use a drip pan so catch the bacon grease.  It that grease hits the flames, then you&#8217;ll get flare ups and catch the whole thing on fire.  Very unsafe, plus an extreme waste of good pork!!!!</p>
		</div><!-- format text -->

		</dd>



	
