			<dt class="comment ">
		<span class="comment_author"><a href='http://hotsaucedaily.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Brian Meagher</a></span>
		<span class="comment_time">January 29, 2009</span>
		</dt>
		<dd class="comment ">
		<div class="format_text">
		<p>@Hackett &#8211; There&#8217;s no reason you can&#8217;t smoke this in a Weber Kettle charcoal grill.<br />
Simply build the fire (low-med) off to one side of the kettle. Shoot for 225 degrees or so.<br />
Don&#8217;t forget some hickory wood on the fire.<br />
Place a drip pan on the other side, and place the bacon monster over that pan.  Get the internal temp to 165 after a few hours and you&#8217;re good. Jason&#8217;s took 2.5 hours.</p>
<p>Good luck!</p>
		</div><!-- format text -->

		</dd>



	
