		<p>Just finished my second try at this a week or so ago.  Just as good (maybe a little bit better) the second time.  Lessons learned:  1) I took sweet onion, sliced and carmalized it then let cool.  Added to inner crumble.  2) From Jan 2, 2009 comment, did all layers but first on parchment.  So much easier to roll very tight and then placed onto the first bacon layer.  </p>
