		<div class="format_text">
		<p>[...] The Bacon Explosion is one of the most decadent things I have seen since the Turducken. (See below.) The Bacon Explosion is a recipe made famous by a team of Kansas City BBQ experts called Burnt Finger BBQ. An interesting-looking meatloaf-type dish, it consists of strips of bacon tightly woven into a square mat, which is seasoned and then rolled around a filling of ground Italian sausage and cooked bacon pieces. The 4 pound loaf is then transferred to a backyard smoker, and cooked for 2-3 hours, slathered in BBQ sauce. It is said to contain at least 5,000 calories and 500 grams of fat. This is a link to the original recipe. <a href="http://www.bbqaddicts.com/blog/recipes/bacon-explosion/" rel="nofollow">http://www.bbqaddicts.com/blog.....explosion/</a> [...]</p>
		</div><!-- format text -->

