			<dt class="comment ">
		<span class="comment_author">Brian</span>
		<span class="comment_time">September 7, 2010</span>
		</dt>
		<dd class="comment ">
		<div class="format_text">
		<p>Here is a twist you might try everybody if you have not already, Weave the bacon, 1.5 to 2lbs Turkey Tenderloin pounded flat between plastic. Put that on the bacon weave and season it with whatever. Next put chopped spinached leaves on the Turkey. This will enhance the bacon flavor in the turkey. Last thinly slice a block of cream cheese and layer over the spinach, turkey and bacon. Now roll this sum of a gun up and get some toothpicks and will look like a football. Toothpicks will help hold together. Now smoke it, (Good Luck Getting it Lit&#8230;. Just kidding) for about 3 to 3.5 hours or until to temperature. Let stand 20 minutes and slice. Hmmmmm Hmmmmm</p>
		</div><!-- format text -->

